==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Carboxide
<hw>Car*box"ide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Carbon</ets>
+ <ets>oxide</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A compound of carbon
and oxygen, as carbonyl, with some element or radical; <as>as, potassium
<ex>carboxide</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Potassium carboxide</b></col>, <cd>a grayish explosive
crystalline compound, <chform>C6O6K</chform>, obtained by passing carbon
monoxide over heated potassium.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Carboxyl</ent>⟦br⟧
